# Voyagair Project Rules

## Python
- Use Pydantic v2 models for all data structures
- All provider and search code must be async
- Use LiteLLM for LLM calls (supports OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini)
- Config loaded from `.env.local` or `.env` via python-dotenv
- Rate limiting via pyrate-limiter, caching via diskcache
- Default LLM model configurable via LLM_MODEL env var

## TypeScript/Frontend
- Vite + TypeScript frontend in `frontend/`
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS app in `voyagair/app/`
- Shared resources in `shared/` (CSS variables, schema files)
- No frameworks -- vanilla DOM manipulation with typed APIs
- Location inputs use grouped autocomplete (airports, cities, countries, regions)

## Style
- No emojis in code or docs unless explicitly requested
- Minimal comments -- only for non-obvious intent
- Use ruff for Python formatting/linting
- Dark theme as default, light theme supported via data-theme attribute

## API
- FastAPI REST + WebSocket endpoints under `/api/`
- Vanilla app served at `/app/`
- Voyage CRUD: POST /api/voyage/new, GET /api/voyage/list, etc.
- Flight search: POST /api/search/flights, WS /api/ws/search

## MCP Integration
- Travel Agent uses MCP tools for supplemental flight information
- Built-in tools wrap existing Voyagair search providers
- External MCP servers configurable via VoyageConfig.travel_agent.mcp_servers
